This paper is about incorporating gender information into neural machine translation (NMT) systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves training NMT models, which could place it in sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
